00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:45,820
 We celebrate here this morning a new narrative of hope in this world that literally changes

231
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:48,340
 everything.

232
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:50,260
 That's Christmas.

233
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:52,340
 That's worth celebrating.

234
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:55,540
 That my friends is joy to the world.

235
00:15:55,540 --> 00:16:01,060
 I wonder whether you would stand with me and I would love to pray over us.

236
00:16:01,060 --> 00:16:08,060
 Father, thank you so much for each person gathered here today.

237
00:16:08,060 --> 00:16:11,300
 Children, adults, everybody in between.

238
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:15,180
 Lord, you have met us so beautifully.

239
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:21,500
 And Lord, we are so grateful that you carry this name, the name of Jesus.

240
00:16:21,500 --> 00:16:26,060
 And Father, as we stand before you in this moment here on Christmas day, I want to maybe

241
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:32,220
 take a moment to be like Peter before the crippled man at the gate of beautiful.

242
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:40,380
 And so Lord, I want to pray over any family here where sickness or disease is having a

243
00:16:40,380 --> 00:16:43,820
 hold on that family this Christmas time.

244
00:16:43,820 --> 00:16:49,660
 Maybe a recent diagnosis, maybe an ongoing disease or sickness.

245
00:16:49,660 --> 00:16:53,020
 Maybe people in the wider family not feeling how they should be.

246
00:16:53,020 --> 00:16:57,380
 Father, as the Vine community, we stand together not in the power of our name.

247
00:16:57,380 --> 00:17:02,100
 But Lord, we want to pray for these family members who maybe are not feeling the best

248
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,100
 that they could feel.

249
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:11,620
 We say in the name of Jesus, would you bring healing, restoration, would sickness go in

250
00:17:11,620 --> 00:17:12,620
 the name of Jesus?

251
00:17:12,620 --> 00:17:18,380
 Lord, would you strengthen these family members of ours that we bring before you now in name

252
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:20,280
 and thought?

253
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:26,260
 In the name of Jesus, would you change their lives?

254
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:30,740
 And perhaps there are people in your life and in your sphere of influence that you long

255
00:17:30,740 --> 00:17:33,060
 to see come to Jesus.

256
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:35,860
 Father, we thank you for each of these.

257
00:17:35,860 --> 00:17:39,980
 Maybe you can just bring them to mind in your heart right now.

258
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:44,700
 Lord, as we think about these people in our sphere of influence that we long to be in

259
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:51,260
 relationship with you, Lord, there is no other name by which they can be saved other than

260
00:17:51,260 --> 00:17:52,260
 yours.

261
00:17:52,260 --> 00:18:00,820
 So we pray in the name of Jesus, Lord, that you would move mountains to find them, that

262
00:18:00,820 --> 00:18:05,900
 you would use us to share the good news with them, or you would use people around them

263
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:09,400
 to do so, but that you would find them.

264
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:13,900
 They would find you and salvation would come to this house.

265
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,980
 We pray that in the name of Jesus.

266
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:20,820
 And finally, I want to pray for anyone here in this room right now and in our overflow

267
00:18:20,820 --> 00:18:23,220
 area.

268
00:18:23,220 --> 00:18:24,900
 Maybe someone's brought you to church today.

269
00:18:24,900 --> 00:18:29,620
 Maybe you've come and maybe you don't normally come to church and maybe this whole religion

270
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:34,780
 thing seems strange to you, but I want to declare before you that there is a narrative

271
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:39,200
 of hope that is in this world that is far greater than any narrative that is currently

272
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,060
 around your life.

273
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:49,060
 Any narrative of despair or struggle or hardship, any narrative of anxiety or fear or worry,

274
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:57,220
 the name of Jesus is a name that brings a new narrative of hope, of life, of goodness,

275
00:18:57,220 --> 00:18:59,260
 of joy.

276
00:18:59,260 --> 00:19:06,320
 And for every person here, that is open to you this morning.

277
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:11,140
 And so I want to boldly pray for you, if that is for you.

278
00:19:11,140 --> 00:19:15,260
 Maybe you're here this morning and you're like, "I don't have all the answers.

279
00:19:15,260 --> 00:19:23,500
 I don't know exactly what this is all about, but I recognize that I need hope in my life.

280
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:26,260
 I recognize I need something new for me.

281
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:28,380
 I'm tired of the narrative of despair."

282
00:19:28,380 --> 00:19:36,100
 And if that's you, it's just a simple prayer in your heart this morning.

283
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:40,860
 One of the things that we know about Christmas is that there's this idea of Emmanuel, God

284
00:19:40,860 --> 00:19:41,860
 with us.

285
00:19:41,860 --> 00:19:46,660
 And the simple prayer for you this morning is, "Lord, would you just make yourself known

286
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:48,740
 to me?

287
00:19:48,740 --> 00:19:51,820
 Would you reveal your presence to me?

288
00:19:51,820 --> 00:20:02,740
 If you're real, would you, even today, show me something of who you are?"

289
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:04,220
 That's a powerful little prayer.

290
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:06,100
 A simple thing to do.

291
00:20:06,100 --> 00:20:11,860
 And I believe that if you pray that prayer honestly, God will always honor that prayer.

292
00:20:11,860 --> 00:20:19,180
 And that he will come and meet you, bring his presence to you, bring you peace and love

293
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:20,980
 and joy.

294
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:25,980
 And through that, show you how to repent of all of the things that you've carried and

295
00:20:25,980 --> 00:20:32,180
 that have weighed you down, the sin that entangles us all and brings us into new life and joy

296
00:20:32,180 --> 00:20:35,500
 within him.

297
00:20:35,500 --> 00:20:40,220
 So Lord, for any brother and sister here in this room, where that's their prayer this

298
00:20:40,220 --> 00:20:46,500
 morning, Lord, we celebrate this gift of salvation with them.

299
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:48,260
 We ask, Lord, that you would meet them today.

300
00:20:48,260 --> 00:20:52,620
 And that maybe they would ask the person that they've come with, "Hey, I prayed that prayer.

301
00:20:52,620 --> 00:20:54,540
 Pastor Andrew asked us to pray.

302
00:20:54,540 --> 00:20:57,860
 I don't have all the answers, but would you help me on the next steps?"

303
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:05,260
 And that, Lord, we would see salvation, not just in the name of a child, but in the presence

304
00:21:05,260 --> 00:21:08,220
 of our families.

305
00:21:08,220 --> 00:21:10,860
 And that would be a beautiful thing.

306
00:21:10,860 --> 00:21:16,460
 We thank you for this, for the joy that this brings us here on Christmas Day.

307
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:19,740
 And we just pray this in Jesus' name.

308
00:21:19,740 --> 00:21:20,740
 Everyone says?

309
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:21,740
 Amen.

310
00:21:21,740 --> 00:21:22,740
 Amen.

311
00:21:22,740 --> 00:21:25,860
 And we continue to worship together as we celebrate the birth of Jesus.

312
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:29,220
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

